enhanced_by.reason: Both methods validate that an object is not null and throw a ValidationException if it is.
Both methods validate that an object is not null but with the ability to customize the exception message.
Both methods validate that an object is not null and return the object, with the ability to customize the exception message.
Calling notNull(Object) before ensureNotNull(Object) can help ensure the object is not null before proceeding.
Calling notNull(Object, String) before ensureNotNull(Object) can help ensure the object is not null before proceeding, with a customizable message.
Calling ensureNotNull(Object, String, Object...) before ensureNotNull(Object) can help ensure the object is not null before proceeding, with a customizable message.
